cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a framework for learning disentangled face features with minimal supervision, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed features on face attribute recognition and face generation/editing, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
